ODM Party started its NDC programme on Saturday by remembering their late heroes and heroines who have contributed to the success of the party. The Party's Communication Director Philip Etale said that those that were lost along the way are still remembered for immensely contributing to the party's achievements. The late Otieno Kajwang' who was known for his famous campaign song "Bado Mapambano" made the highlights after delegates sang the song after his photo appeared on the screen. Among the remembered ODM Party members are: 1. Otieno Kanjwang' 2. Dr. Odhiambo Mbai, Devolution Expert 3. Monica Amolo, ODM Chairperson - Homa Bay 4. Dr. Adhu Awiti, Former MP - Karachuonyo 5. Mama Grace Mboja, Womam Leader - Kilifi 6. David Too, MP Ainamoi 7. Mugabe Were 8. William Ole Ntimama 9. Kipkalya Arap Kones 10. Joseph Nkaissery 11. Lorna Laboso 12. Orwa Ojode 13. Ken Okoth Raila Odinga's son Fidel Odinga was also remembered among other leaders.